      • char2CharEntrySet

        public ObjectSortedSet<Char2CharMap.Entry> char2CharEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Char2CharMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Char2CharMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        char2CharEntrySet in interface Char2CharMap
        Specified by:

        Overrides:
